To install the package, make sure you have Python v3.7 or higher installed.  

In the current package directory, first create a virtual environment, running: 
    $python3 -m venv .venv     #N.B ‘.venv’ generic hidden directory name

Activate the virtual environment:  
    $source .venv/bin/activate

Then, to install the package with its requirements do:  
    $python3 -m pip install .  

Later, to exit the virtual environment, simply do:  
    $deactivate  

For each source package modification, run again: 
    $python3 -m pip install .  